<emphasis box="[1010,1059,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">et al</emphasis>
., 2015)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1398,2036]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
1. Tegmina with distinctly smaller cells in costal area and with vein MA not fused with Rs (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1151,1398,1420]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1114,1138]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,310,1090]" captionTargetId="figure-80@38.[151,1436,309,1091]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 22. Quiva species. A–D. Q. (P.) angieae. E–H. Q. (Q.) pulchella. I–K. Q. (Q.) diaphana. L–N. Q. (Q.) buhrnheimi. O–Q. Q. (Q.) sharovi. R–T. Q. (Q.) abacata. U–W. Q. (Q.) gutjahrae. A, E. Male habitus in lateral view. B, F, I, L, O, R, U. Frons. C, G, J, M, P, S, V. Subgenital plates. D, H, K, N, Q, T, W. Cerci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876267/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 22A</figureCitation>
); male cerci with outer branch distinctly shorter than inner branch (
<figureCitation box="[577,665,1427,1449]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1114,1138]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,310,1090]" captionTargetId="figure-80@38.[151,1436,309,1091]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 22. Quiva species. A–D. Q. (P.) angieae. E–H. Q. (Q.) pulchella. I–K. Q. (Q.) diaphana. L–N. Q. (Q.) buhrnheimi. O–Q. Q. (Q.) sharovi. R–T. Q. (Q.) abacata. U–W. Q. (Q.) gutjahrae. A, E. Male habitus in lateral view. B, F, I, L, O, R, U. Frons. C, G, J, M, P, S, V. Subgenital plates. D, H, K, N, Q, T, W. Cerci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876267/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 22C</figureCitation>
); male subgenital plate with rather long styli and shallow emargination between them (
<figureCitation box="[287,373,1456,1478]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1114,1138]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,310,1090]" captionTargetId="figure-80@38.[151,1436,309,1091]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 22. Quiva species. A–D. Q. (P.) angieae. E–H. Q. (Q.) pulchella. I–K. Q. (Q.) diaphana. L–N. Q. (Q.) buhrnheimi. O–Q. Q. (Q.) sharovi. R–T. Q. (Q.) abacata. U–W. Q. (Q.) gutjahrae. A, E. Male habitus in lateral view. B, F, I, L, O, R, U. Frons. C, G, J, M, P, S, V. Subgenital plates. D, H, K, N, Q, T, W. Cerci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876267/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 22C</figureCitation>
)............................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castaneda, 2013 Tegmina" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Quiva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angieae" subGenus="Paraquiva">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[960,1191,1456,1478]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
